


SHORT VS. LONG VOWEL

    BEFORE ACCENT

        occidentēs ~ occīdentēs
        dīcāmus ~ dicāmus
        intercidisse ~ intercīdisse

    ON ACCENT
        uenī ~ uēnī
        pedis ~ pēdis
        miseram ~ mīseram
        labrum ~ lābrum
        os ~  ōs
        anus ~  ānus
        uenimus ~  uēnimus
        malum ~  mālum

    AFTER ACCENT
        caussa ~ caussā
        foris ~ forīs
        mane ~ manē
        sagitta ~ sagittā
        patri(s) sunt haec ~ patrī sunt haec

    WITH ACCENT MOVE
        loquere ~ loquēre
        dūcere ~ dūcēre

SINGLE VZ. GEMINATED CONSONANT



GEMINATED CONSONANT VS. LONG VOWEL

    currō ~ cūrō
    palla ~ pāla



